# Projocalypse styling — Tailwind + shadcn only

**Tailwind CSS** for all styling. **shadcn/ui** pattern for interactive primitives. Do not introduce other CSS frameworks or per-component stylesheets.

Related: **`projocalypse-stack.mdc`**, **`projocalypse-frontend-design`** skill.

## Allowed

| What | Where |
|------|--------|
| Tailwind utility classes | `className` on any component |
| `cn()` helper | `src/lib/utils.ts` — merge/override classes |
| shadcn/ui primitives | `src/components/ui/` — Radix + `cva` + Tailwind (Button, Dialog, Input, …) |
| Theme tokens & base styles | `src/styles/globals.css` only — `@theme`, resets, fonts |
| Third-party component CSS | Single `@import` in `globals.css` when required (e.g. `react-day-picker`) |
| Inline `style` | **Only** for dynamic values that cannot be expressed as utilities (e.g. `backgroundColor: project.color`) |

## Required patterns

- **New interactive UI** — add or extend a primitive under `src/components/ui/` using the existing shadcn pattern (`forwardRef`, `cva`, Radix slot/primitive, `cn()`).
- **Feature components** — compose from `src/components/ui/*` + Tailwind; no bespoke button/input/dialog implementations.
- **Variants** — use `class-variance-authority` in `ui/` components, not ad-hoc conditional class strings for shared primitives.
- **Icons** — `lucide-react` (already in stack); size/color via Tailwind classes.

## Forbidden (unless user explicitly requests an exception)

- CSS Modules (`*.module.css`)
- Styled-components, Emotion, Linaria, vanilla-extract
- Component-scoped `.css` / `.scss` files under `src/components/`
- UI libraries that ship their own styles (MUI, Chakra, Ant Design, Bootstrap)
- Global `<style>` tags or injected stylesheets in components
- Replacing Tailwind with `@apply` blocks in new CSS files

## Adding a missing shadcn component

1. Match existing files in `src/components/ui/` (kebab-case filename, PascalCase export).
2. Use Radix primitive + `cva` + `cn()` — copy structure from `button.tsx` or `dialog.tsx`.
3. Add any new theme tokens to `@theme` in `globals.css`, not hard-coded hex in feature code.
4. `pnpm add` only the Radix package needed; do not add alternate styling deps.

## When editing

- Prefer extending an existing `ui/` component over duplicating markup/styles in feature folders.
- Keep `globals.css` limited to tokens, resets, and unavoidable third-party imports — not feature layout.
